'''David Sherman''' ([[February 27]], [[1940s#1944|1944]]&mdash;[[November 16]], [[2022]]) was an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] author of [[Wikipedia:Science fiction|science-]] and [[Wikipedia:Military fiction|military fiction]]. He was a [[Wikipedia:Vietnam veteran|Vietnam veteran]] who drew on his own combat experience for much of his writing, and he co-wrote many books with [[Dan Cragg]], including the [[2004]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' novel ''[[Jedi Trial]]''.<ref name="In Memoriam" />

